cancel(Execution) - Method in interface com.github.dm.jrt.runner.Runner
Cancels the specified execution if not already run.
Note that the method will have no effect in case the runner does not maintain a queue or the specified execution has been already processed at the moment of the call.
Note also that, in case the same execution has been added more than one time to the runner queue, when the method returns, the queue will not contain the execution instance anymore, with the consequence that the Runnable.run() method will never be called.
